For the payable constructor function.
- the state variable owner will be updated to 0.
- When the ether just received (i.e., msg.value) is 0:
  - the state variable admin will be updated to caller.

For the changeFeeAccount function, it has one argument and its type is address.

For the changeFeeTake function, it has one argument and its type is uint256.
- For admin, and the first argument is smaller than 0x1a055690d9db80000:
  - the state variable feetake will be updated to the first argument.

For the payable deposit function.
- the tokens from owner to caller will be updated to (the ether just received (i.e., msg.value)+the tokens from owner to caller).

For the withdraw function, it has one argument and its type is uint256.
- When the first argument is not greater than the tokens from owner to caller:
  - the tokens from owner to caller will be updated to (the tokens from owner to caller-the first argument).
  - it transfers ether valued the first argument to caller.

For the depositToken function, it has 2 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256.
- When the first argument is not 0:
  - it calls an external function transferFrom of the first argument with the following argument list: caller, the address of this contract, and the second argument.
  - When the call or transfer succeeds:
    - the tokens from the first argument to caller will be updated to (the second argument+the tokens from the first argument to caller).

For the withdrawToken function, it has 2 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256.
- When the first argument is not 0, and the second argument is not greater than the tokens from the first argument to caller:
  - the tokens from the first argument to caller will be updated to (the tokens from the first argument to caller-the second argument).
  - it calls an external function transfer of the first argument with the following argument list: caller, and the second argument.

For the order function, it has 6 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256, address, uint256, uint256, uint256.
- it statically calls an external function fallback of 0x2 with the following argument list: 12 V73@0x17fb@0x17d0 8, 24 V42@0x1fd@0x1ea 8, 4 V49@0x20a@0x1ea 28, 4 V52@0x210@0x1ea 28, and 0 or 4 V55@0x215@0x1ea 28 and 0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff00000000, and gets the returned value as v0.
- When the call or transfer succeeds:
  - the orders from caller to v0 will be updated to 1.

For the amountFilled function, it has 10 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256, address, uint256, uint256, uint256, address, uint8, bytes32, bytes32.
- it statically calls an external function fallback of 0x2 with the following argument list: 12 V88@0x17fb@0x17d0 8, 24 V42@0x369@0x356 8, 4 V49@0x377@0x356 28, 4 V52@0x37d@0x356 28, and 0 or 4 V55@0x383@0x356 28 and 0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff00000000.

For the cancelOrder function, it has 9 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256, address, uint256, uint256, uint256, uint8, bytes32, bytes32.
- it statically calls an external function fallback of 0x2 with the following argument list: 12 V90@0x17fb@0x17d0 8, 24 V48@0x29c@0x289 8, 4 V55@0x2a9@0x289 28, 4 V58@0x2af@0x289 28, and 0 or 4 V61@0x2b5@0x289 28 and 0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff00000000, and gets the returned value as v1.
- When the call or transfer succeeds:
  - When the orders from caller to v1 is not 0:
    - the orderfills from caller to v1 will be updated to the second argument.
  - When the orders from caller to v1 is 0:
    - it statically calls an external function 0x00A3(194 of 0x1 with the following argument list: the 7-th argument, the 8-th argument, and the 9-th argument, and gets the returned value as v0.
    - When the call or transfer succeeds, and for v0:
      - the orderfills from caller to v1 will be updated to the second argument.

For the availableVolume function, it has 10 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256, address, uint256, uint256, uint256, address, uint8, bytes32, bytes32.
- it statically calls an external function fallback of 0x2 with the following argument list: 12 V97@0x17fb@0x17d0 8, 24 V51@0x64e@0x63b 8, 4 V58@0x65c@0x63b 28, 4 V61@0x662@0x63b 28, and 0 or 4 V64@0x668@0x63b 28 and 0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff00000000, and gets the returned value as v0.
- When the call or transfer succeeds, and the orders from the 7-th argument to v0 is 0:
  - it statically calls an external function 0x00A3(194 of 0x1 with the following argument list: the 8-th argument, the 9-th argument, and the 10-th argument.

For the testTrade function, it has 12 arguments and the type of each argument is as follows: address, uint256, address, uint256, uint256, uint256, address, uint8, bytes32, bytes32, uint256, address.
- When the 11-th argument is not greater than the tokens from the first argument to the 12-th argument:
  - it statically calls an external function fallback of 0x2 with the following argument list: 12 V123@0x17fb@0x17d0 8, 24 V51@0x448@0x435 8, 4 V58@0x456@0x435 28, 4 V61@0x45c@0x435 28, and 0 or 4 V64@0x462@0x435 28 and 0xffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff00000000, and gets the returned value as v0.
  - When the call or transfer succeeds, and the orders from the 7-th argument to v0 is 0:
    - it statically calls an external function 0x00A3(194 of 0x1 with the following argument list: the 8-th argument, the 9-th argument, and the 10-th argument.
